[{"id":"VR792791","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two diagrams of a group of point charges placed on the corners of a square. The first diagram is labeled “Initial Positions” and shows point charge 1 with a charge of negative q on the bottom left corner of the square and point charge 2 with a charge of positive q on the bottom right corner of the square. The second diagram is labeled “Final Positions” and it is identical to the first diagram, but now additionally includes a third point charge with a charge of positive q which is moved from far away horizontally to the right to end at the top right corner of the square.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR792791.g04.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two point charges are fixed in place at adjacent corners of a square, as shown in the figure labeled “Initial Positions.” Point Charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> has a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"negative q\"><math alttext=\"negative q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></math></span></span> and Point Charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> has a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span>. A third point charge, Point Charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span>, also has a charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"positive q\"><math alttext=\"positive q\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mpadded><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></mpadded></math></span></span> and is initially far away from point charges <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. An external force then moves Point Charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> along the straight-line path indicated by the arrowheads in the figure labeled “Final Positions.” Which of the following correctly describes whether the change <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta U sub 1 2 3, end sub\"><math alttext=\"delta U sub 1 2 3, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>123</mn></msub></math></span></span> in electric potential energy of the three-point charge system and the work <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub 1 and 2 on 3\"><math alttext=\"W sub 1 and 2 on 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mtext>1&amp;2</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>on</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>3</mtext></mrow></msub></math></span></span> done by point charges <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> on Point Charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> are positive or negative as Point Charge <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"3\"><math alttext=\"3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>3</mn></math></span></span> is being moved into place?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup align:center cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:40\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:70\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:70\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"delta U sub 1 2 3, end sub\"><math alttext=\"delta U sub 1 2 3, end sub\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Δ</mi><msub><mi>U</mi><mn>123</mn></msub></math></span></span></th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"W sub 1 and 2 on 3\"><math alttext=\"W sub 1 and 2 on 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>W</mi><mrow><mtext>1&amp;2</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>on</mtext><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>3</mtext></mrow></msub></math></span></span></th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody valign:middle\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Positive</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Positive</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Positive</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Negative</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Negative</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Positive</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Negative</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Negative</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR792791_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":1}]